If you are really sure that it holds `TChild` objects only and you won&#39;t add any other objects to it after the cast (`List` is read-only, not immutable), then you can just do an unchecked cast like this:

```kotlin
fun &lt;TChild : BaseType&gt; castList(list: List&lt;BaseType&gt;, clazz: KClass&lt;TChild&gt;): List&lt;TChild&gt; {
    @Suppress(&quot;UNCHECKED_CAST&quot;)
    return list as List&lt;TChild&gt;
}
```
If you prefer to actually check types of items while casting then do:

```kotlin
fun &lt;TChild : BaseType&gt; castList(list: List&lt;BaseType&gt;, clazz: KClass&lt;TChild&gt;): List&lt;TChild&gt; {
    return list.map { clazz.cast(it) }
}
```
Just note the second solution creates a copy of the list, so this is not exactly casting. This is important if you intend to modify the original list after casting, because, as I said, `List` is not immutable, but read-only.

